Built‑in Azure Policy (recommended)
Policy name: Allowed locations
Policy ID: e56962a6-4747-49cd-b67b-bf8b01975c4c

Category: Governance
Effect: Deny (recommended)
Audit (visibility only)

What it does

Blocks resource deployments if location is not in the approved list
Evaluated at create and update time

This policy is Microsoft‑maintained, supported, and audit‑accepted

How to configure it (Azure Portal)
Step 1: Open Azure Policy

Azure Portal → Policy
Go to Definitions
Search for Allowed locations

Step 2: Assign the policy

Click Allowed locations
Select Assign
Scope: Management Group (best practice) or Subscription

Step 3: Configure allowed regions
In Parameters → Allowed locations, enter approved regions:
Example:
[  "eastus",  "westeurope",  "centralindia"]

Use Azure region names, not display names

Examples:

✅ centralindia
❌ Central India


Step 4: Set enforcement

Effect → Deny
Assign the policy

From this point onward:

Deployments outside these regions are blocked
Existing resources unaffected (unless updated)
